{{Infobox UNESCO World Heritage Site | image = Hagi Castle Town Aerial photograph.1976.jpg | image_upright = 1.2 | caption = Aerial photograph of [[Hagi Castle]] Town | location = [[Japan]] | includes = | criteria = {{UNESCO WHS type|(ii), (iv)}}(ii), (iv) | ID = 1484 | coordinates = {{coord|34|25|50|N|131|24|44|E|display=title, inline|format=dms}} | year = 2015 | area = {{convert|306.66|ha|acre|abbr=on}} | buffer_zone = {{convert|2,408.33|ha|acre|abbr=on}} | locmapin = World | map_caption = }} {{nihongo|'''Sites of Japan’s Meiji Industrial Revolution: Iron and Steel, Shipbuilding and Coal Mining'''|明治日本の産業革命遺産 製鉄・鉄鋼、造船、石炭産業|Meiji nihon no sangyōkakumei isan: seitetsu, tekkō, zōsen, sekitan sangyō}} are a group of historic sites that played an important part in the industrialization of [[Japan]] in the [[Bakumatsu]] and [[Meiji period|Meiji]] periods, and are part of the [[industrial heritage]] of Japan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1484/|title=Sites of Japan’s Meiji Industrial Revolution: Iron and Steel, Shipbuilding and Coal Mining |publisher=[[UNESCO]] |accessdate=5 July 2015}}</ref> In 2009 the monuments were submitted jointly for inscription on the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage List]] under criteria [[World Heritage Site#Cultural criteria|ii, iii, and iv]]. The sites were accepted at the 39th UNESCO World Heritage session.
Eight areas are registered, with thirty component sites:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kyuyama.jp/e/action/a02.html |title=To be World Heritage: Updated Situation |publisher=Kyuyama |accessdate=17 February 2012}}</ref><ref name="Emergence">{{cite web |url=http://www.kyuyama.jp/e/action/teigensyoE.pdf |title=Emergence of Industrial Japan: Kyushu - Yamaguchi |publisher=Kyuyama |accessdate=17 February 2012}}</ref>
